title: Determination of cross section of alpha-induced nuclear reaction on natural Cr and Zr by stacked foil activation for thin layer activation analysis

x4freetext: Determination of cross section of alpha-induced
nuclear reaction on natural Cr and Zr by stacked foil
activation for thin layer activation analysis

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.103, p.261 (1995)

x4codes.hlp: Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics, Kolkata, India
Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai, India
Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics, Kolkata, India

x4freetext: Variable Energy Cyclotron at Kolkata.
The beam current was measured through a Faraday
cup and a copper monitoring foil was always put before
the stacked target in each irradiation to check the
beam current measurement
The irradiation was carried out with about
400 nA for 4 hours in the Zr stack and 200 nA for four
hours in the Cr and V stacks.
The time dependent counting measurements were
taken at least twice for each radioisotope to follow
the half-life.
The data were taken from ORNL-CPX-2, 1964
Alice 85/300

x4freetext: - By compiler - the authors could not measure
production cross section of Fe-52-m (t1/2=46 sec).
- By author - Fe-52 is produced only from Cr-50 by
(alpha,2n) reaction channel up to 40 MeV because
threshold energy of another possible channel
Cr-52(alpha,4n) is 39.8 MeV.
The chromium content determined in the target foils was
in range of 125-250 ug/cm2.
